# Airspace Germany

General briefings for flying in German airspace

· Flight planning

· Finding pre-validated IFR routes
☐

<!-- PageBreak -->


## Flight planning

<!-- PageBreak -->

<!-- PageHeader="Flight planning" -->


# Finding pre-validated IFR routes

There are different websites available where you can find up to date and Eurocontrol valid IFR
routes that you can fly on VATSIM. Due to the complex structure of European airspace it's
important to use correct routes when flying online.

If a controller has sent you a link to this page, please use one of the tools below to find
and refile a suitable route for your flight!

Do not use any routes suggested by the MSFS 2024 planning tool! Only copy routes
provided from a source below into the planning tool.


## dispatch.simbrief.com (free account required)

SimBrief is still the best free tool available for flight planning. You can plan your full flight or search
and copy a route provided (provide an origin and destination airport as well as an aircraft type to
see suggested routes).

Only use routes that have a blue (CFMU/IFPS valid) or green (real world route) marker!


## 9. @ Real World

☒
Valid for AIRAC 2411

SOBR9F SOBRA Y180 DIK UN857 GIMER UT300 PON UN872 DIDAK AKEMO LAPEX
SEPAL 46NO15W 44NO20W 40NO30W 36N040W 31N045W 26NO50W 21NO55W CITRS
UP533 BNS UW50 KIKAS DOPLO DOPL4E

Real-world route
?


## 10. @ EUROCONTROL

☒
Valid for AIRAC 2411

ULKIG Y180 DIK UN857 GIMER UT300 ELCOB UT176 LGL UN491 UPALO UN585
FEJAC REGHI UN480 ETIKI 47NO15W 46NO20W 39NO30W 32NO40W 27N045W
21NO50W JTHON 17NO55W FOF ONGAL UN669 MASPA TOROP PBL UP533 BNS UW50
KIKAS DOPLO DOPL4E

<!-- PageFooter="IFPS compliant route (AIRAC 2411)" -->

?
<!-- PageBreak -->

<!-- PageHeader="grd.aero-nav.com" -->

Only Eurocontrol valid routings (CFMU valid) that are manually entered by users are available. The
amount of available routes varies a lot and highly depends on the airport you are looking for!


# radarbox.com

For future and previous flights beginning or ending in Europe (within 7 days), the filed route is
available at "Flight Info" on the right tab (select a flight and scroll down in the "Flight Info" section
on the right).

You can look up a previous and future flight numbers for any airport pair at flightaware.com and
use this flight number to find the route on RadarBox.


## eurofpl.eu (free account required)

This advanced website builds new and CFMU valid routes within Europe. Routes to/from Europe to
any other continent will end/begin at the last/first European FIR border. You can look up a
connecting route by using the SimBrief route planner including the last waypoint of the suggested
route and create a new routing.

Only use the "NM proposed" routes and check every routing that is longer than 10% of the great
circle distance on a map. If no suitable route was found, try to change the requested FL or time and
try again.


### EuroFPL Aircraft Setup

First of all you have to set up a new aircraft in your "Aircraft hangar".

You don't need to use the aircraft you would like to fly, it's fine to have one jet and one prop
aircraft that fulfill the basic equipment requirements.

Simply use the following data and it will work fine when creating an aircraft.


## JET AIRCRAFT

<!-- PageBreak -->


## 7 AIRCRAFT IDENTIFICATION

TYPE OF AIRCRAFT

DESCRIPTION

edi-gla.co.uk (free account required)

Route database with previously used real world used routes. Depending on the airport pair, the
available routes can be up to date or some years old.

Always check if you are able to fly the routes with an up to date NAV database before filing it
on VATSIM!

2. The second route is labeled "Eurocontrol" and is also valid for AIRAC 2411. It includes the following waypoints and airways: UKLIG, Y180, DIK, UN857, GIMER, UT300, ELCOB, UT176, LGL, UN491, UPALO, UN585, FEJAC, REGHI, UN480, ETIKI, 47N015W, 46N020W, 39N030W, 32N040W, 27N045W, 21N050W, 17N055W, FOF, ONGAL, UN669, MASPA, TOROP, PBL, UP533, BNS, UW50, KIKAS, DOPLO, DOPL4E.

Both routes are marked as valid for AIRAC 2411, with the first route being a real-world route and the second route being an IFPS compliant route.

**Jet Aircraft Section:**
- **Aircraft Identification:** GLF5
- **Type of Aircraft:** GLF5

- **Wake Turbulence Category:** M (Medium)
- **Equipment:** SDGIRWY / LB1
- **Cruising Speed:** N0450
- **Level:** F510
- **Other Information:** PBN/A1B1D1L1

**Prop Aircraft Section:**
- **Aircraft Identification:** BE58
- **Type of Aircraft:** BE58
- **Description:** PROP
- **Wake Turbulence Category:** L (Light)
- **Equipment:** SDGIRWY / LB1
- **Cruising Speed:** N0200
- **Level:** F250
- **Other Information:** (Blank)

The form includes fields for various technical specifications and identifiers for the aircraft, such as wake turbulence category, equipment codes, cruising speed, and flight level.

indexed_data.content:
Flight planning Finding pre-validated IFR routes There are different websites available where you can find up to date and Eurocontrol valid IFR routes that you can fly on VATSIM. Due to the complex structure of European airspace it's important to use correct routes when flying online. If a controller has sent you a link to this page, please use one of the tools below to find and refile a suitable route for your flight! Do not use any routes suggested by the MSFS 2024 planning tool! Only copy routes provided from a source below into the planning tool. dispatch.simbrief.com (free account required) SimBrief is still the best free tool available for flight planning. You can plan your full flight or search and copy a route provided (provide an origin and destination airport as well as an aircraft type to see suggested routes). Only use routes that have a blue (CFMU/IFPS valid) or green (real world route) marker! 'The image displays two flight routes with their respective waypoints and airways. 

1. The first route is labeled "Real World" and is valid for AIRAC 2411. It includes the following waypoints and airways: SOBR9F, SOBRA, Y180, DIK, UN857, GIMER, UT300, PON, UN872, DIDAK, AKEMO, LAPEX, SEPAL, 46N015W, 44N020W, 40N030W, 36N040W, 31N045W, 26N050W, 21N055W, CITRS, UP533, BNS, UW50, KIKAS, DOPLO, DOPL4E.

2. The second route is labeled "Eurocontrol" and is also valid for AIRAC 2411. It includes the following waypoints and airways: UKLIG, Y180, DIK, UN857, GIMER, UT300, ELCOB, UT176, LGL, UN491, UPALO, UN585, FEJAC, REGHI, UN480, ETIKI, 47N015W, 46N020W, 39N030W, 32N040W, 27N045W, 21N050W, 17N055W, FOF, ONGAL, UN669, MASPA, TOROP, PBL, UP533, BNS, UW50, KIKAS, DOPLO, DOPL4E.

Both routes are marked as valid for AIRAC 2411, with the first route being a real-world route and the second route being an IFPS compliant route.'

indexed_data.content: grd.aero-nav.com Only Eurocontrol valid routings (CFMU valid) that are manually entered by users are available. The amount of available routes varies a lot and highly depends on the airport you are looking for! radarbox.com For future and previous flights beginning or ending in Europe (within 7 days), the filed route is available at "Flight Info" on the right tab (select a flight and scroll down in the "Flight Info" section on the right). You can look up a previous and future flight numbers for any airport pair at flightaware.com and use this flight number to find the route on RadarBox. eurofpl.eu (free account required) This advanced website builds new and CFMU valid routes within Europe. Routes to/from Europe to any other continent will end/begin at the last/first European FIR border. You can look up a connecting route by using the SimBrief route planner including the last waypoint of the suggested route and create a new routing. Only use the "NM proposed" routes and check every routing that is longer than 10% of the great circle distance on a map. If no suitable route was found, try to change the requested FL or time and try again. EuroFPL Aircraft Setup First of all you have to set up a new aircraft in your "Aircraft hangar". You don't need to use the aircraft you would like to fly, it's fine to have one jet and one prop aircraft that fulfill the basic equipment requirements. Simply use the following data and it will work fine when creating an aircraft. JET AIRCRAFT
